CASES DISPOSED OF WITHOUT CONSIDERATION BY THE COURT, FROM OCTOBER 4, 1920, TO AND INCLUDING JANUARY 24, 1921.

No. 138. United States v. Picher Lead Company.

Error to the District Court.of the United States for the Western District of Missouri.- October 5, 1920. Dismissed, on motion of The Solicitor General for the United States. Mr. A. E. Spencer for defendant in error.
